Koko Sarah Malema passed away on Saturday morning at her home in Seshogo, Polokwane. JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader Julius Malema's grandmother has died. Koko Sarah Malema passed away on Saturday morning at her home in Seshogo, Polokwane. Her death comes just weeks after Malema buried his aunt. "We send our revolutionary condolences on behalf of the entire Economic Emancipation Movement to our CIC Julius Malema, the entire Malema family, their relatives and friends. The greatest matriarch and pillar of their strength has fallen; the great tree that provided cooling shades of comfort, love and stability has been uprooted, forever, from their lives," the party said in statement.  Malema is scheduled to address EFF's final rally in Orlando, Soweto, on Sunday.